<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Cost Factors</p>
    <h2>What affects range hood repair cost in Los Angeles</h2>
    <div class="factors-grid">
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128293;</div><h3>Grease buildup &mdash; LA kitchen reality</h3><p>LA households with wok cooking, high-BTU ranges, and frequent frying build up grease much faster than manufacturer cleaning schedules assume. A motor that sounds broken is often just grease-imbalanced. We clean before we diagnose a motor failure.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128268;</div><h3>Ducted vs. ductless</h3><p>Ducted hoods can have duct blockages that make them appear to fail. Ductless hoods need charcoal filter replacement which is maintenance &mdash; not a repair. We assess which type you have and diagnose accordingly.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127963;&#65039;</div><h3>Installation type</h3><p>Under-cabinet hoods are easy to access. Island hoods and integrated cabinet hoods require more access work. Built-in units in custom cabinetry may require removing panels. Labor reflects actual access complexity.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127991;</div><h3>Brand and motor availability</h3><p>Standard brand motors (Broan, NuTone, GE) are widely available. Wolf, Miele, and Gaggenau use proprietary blower assemblies at premium pricing &mdash; quoted separately so you see the real cost.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#9888;&#65039;</div><h3>Duct condition &mdash; fire safety</h3><p>A range hood that works fine but has a grease-clogged duct is a fire hazard. We inspect duct condition on every ducted hood call and advise honestly. Duct cleaning is a separate service quoted before starting.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128204;</div><h3>Root cause first</h3><p>Grease cleaning is always assessed before ordering a motor. If cleaning resolves the noise or suction issue, you pay for labor only &mdash; no part. With separate labor and parts, you see exactly what was needed.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

